Thanks a million to Stack and Niklas - because I&#39;d had to update to 
the proxy-friendly patch, I&#39;d had to mess around with my setup, jars 
etc, and was actually running extracted classes rather than directly 
from heritrix-1.0.4.jar. As everything seemed to start and run fine 
without errors, I hadn&#39;t thought it was a classpath problem.

But, having started a fresh directory, just putting in the jars I 
absolutely needed and generally tidying up, and running directly from 
a proxy-friendly-updated heritrix-1.0.4.jar, the problem seems to 
have been resolved - at least, I now have a crawl running happily 
into the thousands.

Schoolboy error on my part, although slightly worrying at 
how &#39;silent&#39; the problem was. Thanks again, though,

Jim


